# Testing Conventions

Stack: **Vitest** (unit/integration), **Playwright** (e2e in devinity-web), **supertest** (API e2e in devinity-api).

## Running tests

From repo root:

```bash
pnpm test        # turbo run test — all packages/apps
pnpm test:e2e    # turbo run test:e2e
pnpm codeCheck   # npx tsc && pnpm lint (root)
```

Per-app: `pnpm test` inside the app/package directory.

## Vitest — file naming & location

| App / package | Config | Include pattern | Environment |
|---------------|--------|-----------------|-------------|
| take-and-do | `vitest.config.ts` | `src/**/*.test.ts` | `node` |
| devinity-api | `vitest.config.ts` | unit in src; e2e via `vitest.e2e.config.ts` | node |
| devinity-web | `vitest.config.ts` + `@repo/vitest-config/next` | component/unit tests | jsdom |
| @repo/shared | `vitest.config.ts` | `src/**/*.test.ts` | node |

- Co-locate unit tests next to source (`*.test.ts`) or under `src/tests/` for shared helpers.
- Controller tests: `apps/take-and-do/src/server/controllers/tests/`.

## Vitest — patterns

```typescript
import { describe, expect, it, vi } from "vitest";
```

- Mock with `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`.
- take-and-do controller tests: extend `BaseController`, use `NextRequest`, assert status + JSON.
- devinity-api e2e: `@nestjs/testing` `Test.createTestingModule`, `supertest` against `app.getHttpServer()`.
- Prefer testing behavior and HTTP contracts, not implementation details.

## Playwright e2e (devinity-web)

- Location: `apps/devinity-web/test/e2e/*.e2e-spec.ts`
- Run: `pnpm test:e2e` in devinity-web (or root `pnpm test:e2e`).
- Use `@playwright/test` `test` / `expect`; `page.request` for API-level checks.

## What to test

- Helpers and pure functions: unit tests with edge cases.
- `BaseController` route wiring: request/response validation, error mapping.
- New shared `@repo/shared` helpers: add tests under `src/tests/`.
- UI components in `@repo/ui`: add tests when behavior is non-trivial (package has no test script yet — add vitest if introducing tests).

## Do not

- Use Jest APIs — this repo uses Vitest (NestJS `globals.vitest` in eslint nest config).
- Add e2e tests for take-and-do unless Playwright is set up there (currently devinity-web only).
